      • State

        public State()

      • State

        public State(Trial trial,
             FieldMapper fieldMapper,
             java.lang.String values)
        Full constructor takes a Trial, FieldMapper, and String as arguments. The Trial is passed so that each State may be able to identify the Trial to which it belongs The FieldMapper is used to map values from the CSV string to the appropriate field names The String of values is pulled from a CSV file and contains data for each of the fields contained in the trial
        Parameters:
        trial - Indicates the trial to which this state belongs
        fieldMapper - Informs the constructor how to create fields from the String data
        values - Describes all of the values associated with the State (a CSV row)

      • getValue

        public GeneralValue getValue(java.lang.String fieldName,
                             java.lang.String subFieldName)
        Returns the value of a specific field and subfield for this state. If a desired field is without subfields, such as time, an empty String can be passed in as subFieldName
        Parameters:
        fieldName - Specifies the desired field such as "Left_Wrist"
        subFieldName - Specifies the desired subfield such as "z"
        Returns:
        A GeneralValue object representing the value of specified field and subfield in its current State
